 FIRS  The Head of Tax at KPMG, Wole Abayomi, explained the need for tax reforms and bemoaned the  10-year period it took after the previous tax reforms was done, saying it should now be a yearly affair.He also expressed worry that three months after VAIDS’ deadline, no action has been taken by government, “so that those paying their tax accurately would not feel shortchanged.” A representative of Andersen Tax, Chinedu Ezomike, canvassed guidelines on how small businesses in the informal sector can be helped to pay taxes without affecting their operations negatively.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .